# NYC Taxi Data Pipeline

## Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end data engineering pipeline using Apache Airflow, Python, Docker and PostgreSQL.

The pipeline ingests NYC Taxi trip data stored in Parquet format, performs data quality checks and feature engineering, and loads the processed data into PostgreSQL for downstream analysis.

The project was built to showcase practical data engineering skills including:

- Workflow orchestration with Airflow
- ETL pipeline development in Python
- Data quality validation
- Feature engineering
- PostgreSQL integration
- Docker containerisation
- Configuration management using environment variables
- Logging and monitoring
- Automated testing

---

## Key Learnings

This project strengthened my understanding of:

- Workflow orchestration with Airflow
- Containerised development using Docker
- Data quality validation techniques
- PostgreSQL integration and schema management
- Building maintainable Python ETL pipelines
- Testing and configuration management

